04/04/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The government appointed its first foreign minister Thursday (April 3rd) since declaring independence in February.
Former Culture Minister Skender Hyseni, a close ally of the late President Ibrahim Rugova, is assuming the post.
He also served as a spokesman for Kosovo Albanians during the UN-mediated talks on final status.
In other news Thursday, the government adopted a plan for the country's European integration, covering 2008 to 2010.
It outlines actions domestic institutions should take to bring legislation and administration reforms closer to EU standards.
Prime Minister Hashim Thaci has said EU integration is a primary government priority.
(Koha Ditore - 04/04/08;
TV21, KTV, RTK, AFP - 03/04/08)
